Diagnosis. Adult (
Fig. 2
). Wingspan 7.0−13.0 mm. This species is superficially similar to G. m e s o t y p a (Razowski, 1970 ), but
G. alismana
can be distinguished by the socius gradually narrowed in the distal 1 / 3 in the male genitalia (
Fig. 12
), and by the ductus bursae about 2 / 3 the length of the corpus bursae in the female genitalia (
Fig. 21
). In G. m e s o t y p a , the socius is dilated distally in the male genitalia; and the ductus bursae is slightly longer than the corpus bursae in the female genitalia.
